PROJECT PAGE EMULATOR
P25 SmartConnect® Emulation & Research Platform

Overview:
Project PAGE Emulator is a research and development platform designed to emulate a P25 SmartConnect®-capable environment. It enables subscriber radios to establish secure TLS-based connections and interact with a simulated trunked radio system over IP.

The project focuses on protocol-level understanding, system emulation, and interoperability testing of subscriber behavior when operating in a SmartConnect®-enabled environment.

Core Capabilities:
- SmartConnect® TLS session emulation
- Stage 1 / Stage 2 handshake handling
- Radio authentication workflows (RPTL / RPTK / RPTC via DVMFNE)
- System Information delivery (0x50)
- SmartConnect® application message analysis
- Session lifecycle management and cleanup
- Packet capture and protocol inspection

Architecture:
The emulator acts as a bridge between subscriber radios and backend P25 system components. It integrates with DVMProject tools, including DVMHost and DVMFNE, to provide system context, authentication, and control channel data.

Purpose:
This project is intended for:
- Research and development
- Educational use
- Controlled lab testing environments

It provides insight into how subscriber units interact with IP-based extensions of P25 systems and supports development of interoperable solutions.

Acknowledgment:
This project builds upon the foundational work of the DVMProject (Digital Voice Modem Project). Full credit is given to the original authors and contributors for providing the core system components used in this platform.

